The paper deals with linear codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of weak order ideals and monotonicity also suggests a connection to the Combinatorics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's focus on describing sets of codewords and their properties suggests a connection to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
